The article is a statement by the White House Press Secretary on the USA FREEDOM Act. The President had called for reforms to electronic surveillance programs in 2014, and the administration worked with members of Congress to create a compromise that balanced security and privacy. The USA FREEDOM Act prohibited bulk collection and implemented various reforms. The legislation had support from national security professionals, civil libertarians, and members of both parties in the House of Representatives. The Senate took a step forward in passing the act, and the statement calls on them to minimize any delay in implementing it. The statement emphasizes the importance of national security and urges senators to act swiftly and put aside partisan motivations.